"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/991206","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-10-29","<p>The Government has no plans to make any changes to the eligibility for the Nursery Milk Scheme.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2018-10-29T11:42:39.5Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/991206/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/991206/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/991206/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-10-19","School Milk","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, if he will make an assessment of the potential effect on the (a) health of under five year olds and (b) rate of childhood obesity of a reduction in the Nursery Milk Scheme.","false","Biography information for Helen Jones","Warrington North","Helen Jones","181563"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/991208","Home Office","false","2018-10-29","<p>INDECS (the Home Office Immigration and Nationality Department Electronic Computer system) held LC (landing cards) information for arriving passengers at UK ports of entry given check out conditions on arrival (codes 1-4) since 1980. On 14 April 1998, ports ceased to endorse passports or issue/collect embarkation cards on passengers' departure from the UK. These were then made available through the Case Information Database (CID).</p><p>CID was delivered through a phased rollout that was initiated with Asylum cases and was then subsequently rolled out to cater for settlement, enforcement and nationality case working processes as well as assisting Borders. CID has been the source immigration case working system for UKVI since 1998, over this time however the department has digitised application routes through a web-based service called Access UK and are in the process of replacing CID functionality with a new product named ATLAS. Please note that paper files are used alongside these systems to aid case working processes</p><p> </p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-10-29T17:42:18.253Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/991208/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/991208/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/991208/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-10-19","Immigrants: Personal Records","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, when his Department moved from paper to digital for immigration status records.","false","Biography information for Mr David Lammy","Tottenham","Mr David Lammy","181534"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/991209","Home Office","false","2019-01-25","<p>The department has no central record of any incident of damage or loss to large quantities of immigration records in the last twenty years.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2019-01-25T16:58:19.263Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/991209/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/991209/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/991209/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-10-19","Immigrants: Personal Records","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what information his Department holds on incidents of damage or loss to large quantities of immigration records in the last 20 years.","false","Biography information for Mr David Lammy","Tottenham","Mr David Lammy","181535"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/991210","Home Office","false","2019-01-25","<p>The Case Information Database (CID) has been the source immigration case working system since 1998. Individual records of immigration status have therefore been digitised for the last 20 years. CID undergoes nightly back-ups to tape and has replication between the primary and secondary data centres.</p><p>There has been no systematic loss of immigration status records. Where any individual cases are identified or raised as having incorrect or incomplete records, these are treated as an absolute priority.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2019-01-25T17:16:24.527Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/991210/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/991210/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/991210/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-10-19","Immigrants: Personal Records","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what estimate he has made of the number of records of immigration status that have been (a) lost and (b) damaged in the last 20 years.","false","Biography information for Mr David Lammy","Tottenham","Mr David Lammy","181536"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/991211","Home Office","false","2018-10-29","<p>CID undergoes nightly back ups to tape and has replication between the primary and secondary data centres.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-10-29T17:40:59.147Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/991211/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/991211/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/991211/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-10-19","Immigrants: Personal Records","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, by what (a) method and (b) programme are records of immigration status backed-up.","false","Biography information for Mr David Lammy","Tottenham","Mr David Lammy","181537"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/991212","Home Office","false","2018-10-29","<p>The information requested is not available in the format requested and could only be obtained at a disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-10-29T17:44:07.237Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/991212/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/991212/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/991212/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-10-19","Immigrants: Personal Records","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many times his Department has apologised for providing people with incorrect records of their immigration status.","false","Biography information for Mr David Lammy","Tottenham","Mr David Lammy","181538"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/991213","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-10-24","<p>Improving children’s mental and physical health is a top priority for this Government and will be pivotal in our long-term plan for the National Health Service, which we are backing with additional funding of an extra £20.5 billion a year by 2023/24. This follows the existing National Maternity Safety Ambition to halve the 2010 rates of neonatal deaths (as well as stillbirths, maternal deaths and brain injuries that occur during or soon after birth) by 2025, and to achieve a 20% reduction in these rates by 2020. Achieving this ambition would place the United Kingdom amongst other high-income countries with the lowest stillbirth and neonatal mortality rates.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock","181565","2018-10-24T12:26:36.947Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/991213/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/991213/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/991213/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-10-19","Health: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, with reference to Royal College of Paediatrics and Child Health report entitled Child health in 2030 in England: comparisons with other wealthy countries, published in October 2018 what assessment he has made of the implications for his policies of that report; and what steps he plans to take to prevent the negative health outcomes for children and young people by 2030 that are projected within that report.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","181564"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/991214","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-10-24","<p>Improving children’s mental and physical health is a top priority for this Government and will be pivotal in our long-term plan for the National Health Service, which we are backing with additional funding of an extra £20.5 billion a year by 2023/24. This follows the existing National Maternity Safety Ambition to halve the 2010 rates of neonatal deaths (as well as stillbirths, maternal deaths and brain injuries that occur during or soon after birth) by 2025, and to achieve a 20% reduction in these rates by 2020. Achieving this ambition would place the United Kingdom amongst other high-income countries with the lowest stillbirth and neonatal mortality rates.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock","181564","2018-10-24T12:26:36.997Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/991214/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/991214/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/991214/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-10-19","Infant Mortality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, with reference to Royal College of Paediatrics and Child Health report entitled Child health in 2030 in England: comparisons with other wealthy countries, published in October 2018, what plans his Department has to reduce the infant mortality rate in England as a result of the findings of that report.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","181565"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/991215","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-10-24","<p>The Cyber Security Information Sharing Partnership (CiSP) is a joint industry and government initiative set up to exchange cyber threat information in real time, in a confidential and dynamic environment. The benefits of CiSP include giving members a secure environment to engage with industry and government counterparts, supplying early warning of cyber threats, and helping members learn from their experiences and successes of other users. In October 2018 the total number of organisations registered on CiSP is over 6500 and the number of individual users registered is over 11,600.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2018-10-24T15:15:55.193Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/991215/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/991215/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/991215/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-10-19","Cybercrime","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, how many (a) organisations and (b) individuals have signed up to the cyber security information sharing partnership.","false","Biography information for Jo Platt","Leigh","Jo Platt","181641"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/991216","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-10-29","<p>Under the Community Pharmacy Contractual Framework, payment for National Health Service pharmaceutical services does not distinguish between providers; i.e. online pharmacies and ‘bricks and mortar’ pharmacies are paid the same level of fees for services. There are fees which are paid to pharmacy contractors per dispensed item, but there is also a payment which depends on the total monthly volume of prescription items.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-10-29T17:44:47.087Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/991216/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/991216/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/991216/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-10-19","Prescriptions: Costs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, whether the average costs to the public purse of dispensing a prescription item from an internet pharmacy are lower than such costs of dispensing a prescription item from a High Street pharmacy.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","181566"
