li>HES figures are available from 2007-08 onwards. Changes to the figures over time should be interpreted in the context of improvements in data quality and coverage and changes in NHS practice. For example, changes in activity may be due to changes in the provision of care.</li></ol>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2018-10-23T16:19:07.38Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/990275/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/990275/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/990275/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-10-18","Mental Illness: Children and Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, with reference to the Answer of 8 February 2016 to Question 25146 on Mental health services: children, how many people aged 18 and under were admitted to A&E for (a) deliberate self-harm and (b) psychiatric conditions in England in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Bambos Charalambous","Enfield, Southgate","Bambos Charalambous","181292"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/990276","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-10-25","<p>To update the data relating to the prevalence of mental health problems in children and young people, NHS Digital has been conducting a prevalence survey examining the mental health of children and young people. The survey will be published in due course.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2018-10-25T11:44:51.203Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/990276/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/990276/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/990276/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-10-18","Mental Illness: Children and Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, with reference to paragraph 56 of the Transforming Children and Young People’s Mental Health Provision green paper, what progress has been made on updating data relating to the prevalence of mental health problems among children and young people; and when his Department plans to publish that data.","false","Biography information for Bambos Charalambous","Enfield, Southgate","Bambos Charalambous","181293"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/990277","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-10-29","<p>The Ministry of Defence continues to work closely with the Department for Exiting the European Union (DExEU) and other Government Departments to ensure that we can address the implications and realise the opportunities of the UK's withdrawal from the EU, including the effect on our Armed Forces.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","180805","2018-10-29T16:52:34.087Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/990277/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/990277/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/990277/answer","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/990277/answer/previousversion/81214","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","11","Defence","Defence","2018-10-18","Armed Forces","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what assessment his Department has made of the effect on the armed forces of the UK leaving the EU.","false","Biography information for Stewart Malcolm McDonald","Glasgow South","Stewart Malcolm McDonald","181294"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/990278","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-10-26","<p>The British Horserace Authority (BHA) are responsible for the welfare of racehorses at racetracks. The BHA work in collaboration with the RSPCA and World Horse Welfare to make racetracks as safe as possible. The number of racehorse fatalities at racetracks has been falling steadily since 2012, which is welcome. However, whilst I do not see a need for a new regulator, I consider that improvements can be made to further reduce the number of racehorse fatalities each year. I will explore this issue further when I meet BHA to discuss racehorse safety.</p>","Macclesfield","David Rutley",,"2018-10-26T11:13:39.403Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/990278/answer","Biography information for David Rutley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/990278/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/990278/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-10-18","Horses: Animal Welfare","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, if the Government will create a new regulator to address (a) horse welfare and (b) deaths of race horses.","false","Biography information for Mrs Anne Main","St Albans","Mrs Anne Main","181194"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/990279","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-10-23","<p>We believe charities and social enterprises should be fully confident in their right to speak in public debates, and to have a strong campaigning and advocacy role.</p><p> </p><p>The government has not made an assessment on the effect of anti-advocacy clauses in government contracts on charities.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"2018-10-23T13:17:15.01Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/990279/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/990279/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/990279/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-10-18","Charities","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what assessment he has made of the effect of anti-advocacy clauses in government contracts on the effectiveness of (a) large and (b) small charities; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Steve Reed","Croydon North","Mr Steve Reed","181222"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/990280","Cabinet Office","false","2018-10-22","<p>There are no anti-advocacy clauses in the Cabinet Office’s standard contracts.</p>","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden",,"2018-10-22T17:11:17.14Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/990280/answer","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/990280/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/990280/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-10-18","Lobbying","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, if he will take steps to end the use of anti-advocacy clauses in government contracts.","false","Biography information for Mr Steve Reed","Croydon North","Mr Steve Reed","181223"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/990281","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-10-26","<p>Both adult and paediatric adrenaline auto-injectors are available from suppliers for the National Health Service to order for patients. We expect around 70,000 adult adrenaline auto-injectors and 30,000 paediatric adrenaline auto-injectors will have been supplied to the United Kingdom in October.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-10-26T11:46:35.073Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/990281/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/990281/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/990281/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-10-18","Allergies: Medical Equipment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, how many epipens the NHS has available for patients.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","181224"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/990283","Department for Education","false","2018-10-23","<p>The information requested is not held centrally.</p><p> </p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2018-10-23T12:43:26.237Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/990283/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/990283/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/990283/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-10-18","Teachers: EU Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what estimate his Department has made of the number of teachers who are nationals of other EU countries who have left employment in schools in England in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Jo Stevens","Cardiff Central","Jo Stevens","181226"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/990284","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-10-23","<p>The Social Housing Green Paper recognises many landlords play a role that goes beyond their key responsibilities, which includes providing guidance to vital services such as mental health services. Through the Green Paper, we are seeking to gather evidence on the impact of the important role that many social landlords are playing.</p><p>Social housing and more widely, supported housing, provides a vital service for vulnerable people, including people with mental health issues. Safeguarding provision and supply of appropriate supported accommodation is a priority for my department and we will continue to provide capital grant funding to promote new supply of supported housing.</p><p>Our recent announcement confirming funding for all supported housing will stay in Housing Benefit, will also give confidence to the sector to continue to invest in new supply. We are also reviewing oversight arrangements for all supported housing. As a Government, we are investing record levels in mental health, spending £11.98 billion in 2017/18.</p>","South Derbyshire","Mrs Heather Wheeler",,"2018-10-23T13:48:01.567Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/990284/answer","Biography information for Mrs Heather Wheeler","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/990284/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/990284/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-10-18","Supported Housing: Mental Illness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, what steps his Department is taking to ensure the social housing system supports those with mental health problems.","false","Biography information for Graham P Jones","Hyndburn","Graham P Jones","181227"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/990285","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-10-23","<p>Aircraft held in storage are part of the Sustainment Fleet which includes aircraft undergoing upgrade or maintenance.</p><p> </p><p>The number of aircraft available varies from day-to-day according to normal fleet management activities.</p><p> </p><p>Figures for fixed and rotary wing aircraft as at 1 October 2018 are given in the table below. They exclude contractor provided aircraft fleets with the exception of Voyager which is included for completeness.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Aircraft</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Service</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Sustainment Fleet</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Air Seeker (Rivet Joint)</p></td><td><p>RAF</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Atlas A400M</p></td><td><p>RAF</p></td><td><p>5</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Bae 146</p></td><td><p>RAF</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>C-17 Globemaster</p></td><td><p>RAF</p></td><td><p>2</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>C-130J Hercules</p></td><td><p>RAF</p></td><td><p>5</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Hawk T1</p></td><td><p>RAF/RN</p></td><td><p>44</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Hawk T2</p></td><td><p>RAF</p></td><td><p>5</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Lightning</p></td><td><p>RAF</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Sentinel</p></td><td><p>RAF</p></td><td><p>1</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Sentry</p></td><td><p>RAF</p></td><td><p>1</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Shadow/King Air 350</p></td><td><p>RAF</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Tornado</p></td><td><p>RAF</p></td><td><p>9</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Tucano</p></td><td><p>RAF</p></td><td><p>10</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Typhoon</p></td><td><p>RAF</p></td><td><p>35</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Voyager</p></td><td><p>RAF</p></td><td><p>2</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Avenger</p></td><td><p>Navy</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Defender</p></td><td><p>Army</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Islander AL Mk1</p></td><td><p>Army</p><